social_posts.post_text:
Hey everyone💚 I know I’ve been pretty quiet on the jewelry front, but I’m here, trying to get through my long list of pre orders and find a little time to make some new things. I really wanted to have a small holiday update but I unfortunately just don’t have it in me or the time to put my full love and intention into a collection. So I’m taking it slow and creating some new pieces when I can. Like these wolf earrings 🐺 there will probably be lots of wolf pieces coming up for obvious reasons. My next shop update will be in January. These earrings will be available then! Date still to be determined.

I feel like I’ve kind of just been going through the motions these past 2 weeks since Willow’s passing 💔 adjusting to life without her doesn’t feel real. Thank you all again so much for your love and support. For checking in on me and sending Sage so much love as well. This community really is so special to me and I’m so grateful for all of you🐺💕

#wolfjewelry #metalsmith #handcraftedjewelry #wildlifeart #handmade #supportartists #ooakjewelry #ladysmith #inspiredbynature #madewithlove #wolves #womenwhorunwithwolves

Figured I’d share this one to my feed since it’s one of the only new pieces I have ready for the next collection. I can’t wait to be caught up and fully able to throw myself into some new work! I’m almost there though! All moth preorders from the end of October will be shipping by Monday at the latest.

It’s been a really unreal and emotionally intense month. Thank you all for being here and being so patient, supportive and understanding. Sometimes the grief of loosing Willow hits me so hard out of nowhere and I just burst into tears. I wake up in the middle of the night thinking of her and she’s on my mind all day. At the same time we have welcomed a new life into our family and he’s been bringing a lot of joy and healing. You may have already seen him in my stories. His name is Bear 🐻 and he’s pretty special. swipe to see him! 

#handmade #handcrafted #handmadejewelry #malamute #malamutepuppy #metalsmith #botanicaljewelry #sterlingsilver #inspiredbynature #madeinvermont #elvenjewelry

Winter Moths❄️ all moth pre orders have officially been completed and shipped! As much as I have the hardest time with doing repetitive work it sure is satisfying seeing all these detailed pieces together. This is the last batch for awhile and it was some of the best I’ve created yet. I’ll be taking a break from these for a few months at least, unless inspiration strikes. I really love how they turned out as bracelets! 

I’m officially free to start on the next collection. I’m so excited to bring some new work to life. My head and heart definitely need it 💚

Unbelievably in love with these! 🌲💚The amount of detail and the size are perfect for an everyday statement ring. I find that I’m someone that prefers more compact rings and I’m really happy with the amount of life and detail I was able to get on these while also keeping them on the smaller side. 

These are all sized rings. I know I have been known to make alot of made to size rings for the last few years, and as much as I have loved providing that option it tends to completely burn me out and leaves very little time for me to rest in between collections. This year I’ll be doing less made to size unless the design is simple enough to allow it or they are all silver pieces. The average size of my customers has been 6.5-9 so that’s what I’ll be making the most of. Please let me know your ring sizes so I can try and accommodate!

I’ll be making two more of these for next fridays update with moss agates like the stone on the middle ring. So rings sizes are helpful to know for those that are interested 💚

Raffle for Sage’s acl surgery 🐺🐾

Here we go again! As some of you may remember a few years ago one of my huskies had to have two major acl surgeries. This is not something I ever wanted to go through again especially so soon, now with my older husky girl, Sage.

Sage is in good shape and mobility but her right hind leg has a torn acl and will now require surgery. The cost of this procedure has gone up so much and is now estimated to be 6,800$. You all have shown up for me in such big ways over the last few years to help me raise money for Willows surgeries. I'll be putting most of this cost on a credit card because these bills seem like they just keep coming and I don't feel great about have to always ask for help. But if I can raise a fraction of the enormous cost of this surgery is would be helpful. 

Sage will be 10 years old in June and has the energy and activity level of half her age. Also a giant baby brother who will probably end up having 100lbs on her once fully grown. They love to run around and play and I'm constantly worried he's going to knock her over because she isn't as stable as she should be with a torn acl.

You can donate and enter through the link in my bio 💚Cost per entry is 10$ and you may enter as many times as you would like. Example: 20$=2 entries 

Winner will receive this beautiful wolf necklace!

I'll keep the raffle open until next week and draw a winner on Wednesday the 10th.

Sage is scheduled for surgery on Thursday the 11th

Thank you all so much💚 please share this post if you feel called! 🐺

Thank you all so much, again, for sharing and participating in the raffle to raise money for her surgery and for all the well wishes and support you have sent our way! I’m so grateful 💚 I’ll be drawing a winner for the wolf necklace by this weekend!

Keep an eye out for an official update announcement in the coming week! 🌿

Just finished up these two necklaces for the next shop update! Feeling super inspired by everything around me lately🌸

Lupines are a symbol of nature and the cycle of life. They have been used throughout history as symbols of strength and protection. They are often considered symbols of transformation, renewal and imagination 🌿 I first fell in love with lupines while visiting Iceland years ago when I found myself surrounded in a field of them as far as the eye could see. Now I’ve slowly been planting more lupine seeds around every year in hopes of them overtaking the edges of the forest around my home🌱I also just had to make a Rosy Maple moth piece, inspired by the little friend that visited last week. I’m so in love with how both of these turned out and I hope you love them too!

Both of these will be available in the upcoming collection on  Friday 6/23 at 7pm est 🦋

Please like, save, share, comment or engage in any of the above ways. It truly helps so much with getting your favorite artists work seen and with overall encouragement and support. I appreciate you all so much for being here with me💚
